3
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:02,350
Dammit! He isn't holding back!
We gotta get outta here!

4
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:05,310
This place is done for!

5
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:15,820
So that's where the village of those
vile Shandian warriors was hiding?

6
00:02:16,450 --> 00:02:21,580
They're originally from the Blue Sea.
Surely they'd enjoy going home!

7
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:28,960
Now, fall to the world below!

8
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,430
Our village!

9
00:02:42,730 --> 00:02:44,060
That was close!

10
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:47,150
We'd have been burnt to a crisp
if we had left any later!

11
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:57,990
In the name of
Great Warrior Kalgara...

12
00:03:01,330 --> 00:03:04,080
shine the Light of Shandora!

13
00:03:11,170 --> 00:03:12,460
Wyper...

14
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:17,260
You see, your distant ancestor,
Great Warrior Kalgara,

15
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:22,060
had another reason for wanting
to take back our homeland.

16
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:24,100
Another reason?

17
00:03:24,770 --> 00:03:25,810
Indeed.

18
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:29,270
It is Kalgara's single biggest regret.

19
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,770
Listen.

20
00:03:31,770 --> 00:03:36,070
Great Warrior Kalgara
had a very close friend...

21
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:37,950
A close friend?

22
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:45,660
Yes. He met Kalgara
400 years ago. His name was...

23
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:50,750
Mont Blanc Noland!

24
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:00,470
Our tale begins a long,
long time ago...

25
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:03,310
400 years before the present day...

26
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:06,310
and though no written record exists...

27
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:10,520
the legend lives on
from one generation to the next.

28
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:14,190
Get on board, quickly!

29
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,400
The Demon of Shandora is coming!

30
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,240
Hurry! Cast off! Cast off!

31
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,700
But there are still crewmen–

32
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,910
Just get us out to sea already!

33
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:31,040
He's here!

34
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,390
You must be eliminated!

35
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:04,080
Leave all your belongings and go!

36
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:15,670
R-Reporting, Commodore!

37
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:18,460
Our provisions have
finally been exhausted,

38
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:23,340
meaning we're now... lost... at sea...

39
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,680
The cook fainted!

40
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:28,140
Dammit! There's no food left!

41
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:31,310
The commodore dove overboard!

42
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:33,060
This is the Grand Line!

43
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:35,520
Is he gonna drown himself
and abandon us?!

44
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:38,360
Maybe he was so hungry
he chose death instead?

45
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,440
Of course not!

46
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:42,780
He's made it back from
the Grand Line twice! He's a legend!

47
00:05:42,780 --> 00:05:46,240
Then how do you explain these
neatly arranged clothes and shoes?!

48
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:49,040
H-Hey! Someone go check...

49
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,290
Screw that!

50
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,910
This sea is full of monsters!

51
00:05:51,910 --> 00:05:53,370
He's not coming back up!

52
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:55,540
– C-Commodore!
– C-Commodore!

53
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:58,920
He was a pretty nimble guy. Here.

54
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,970
Huh? A rope?

55
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,510
Reel it in.

56
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:08,930
What is this, Commodore?!

57
00:06:08,930 --> 00:06:11,100
You killed this thing underwater?!

58
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,440
Cook it up for us.

59
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:17,440
Slacking off really does dull the senses.

60
00:06:20,570 --> 00:06:22,610
It's a huge storm, Commodore!

61
00:06:22,610 --> 00:06:24,950
Sure seems like it
with all the swaying.

62
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:27,120
"Sure seems like it"? Seriously?!

63
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,990
The yardarm's busted!

64
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:30,830
Where?!

65
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,910
The main mast!

66
00:06:31,910 --> 00:06:36,500
We set out on this voyage
a little over two years ago.

67
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:39,050
It's a miracle that we've 
lasted this long.

68
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,630
Hey, did you hear that just now?

69
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:46,800
Huh? Do you mean the thunder?

70
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,640
No, it was something beautiful...

71
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,810
like a bell...

72
00:06:54,890 --> 00:06:56,810
Priest! Stay with us!

73
00:06:56,810 --> 00:07:01,820
This land is cursed! At this rate,
the Shandians will be completely eradicated!

74
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:05,740
H-How can we save
the village, Priest?!

75
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:08,910
O-Offer... the girl!

76
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:12,620
At the sacrificial altar!

77
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:23,590
How many dead does that make?

78
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:27,180
Over a hundred...

79
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,930
What's going on?!

80
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:32,350
This has never happened
to us before!

81
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:40,770
If I can be of use,
I will gladly give my life.

82
00:07:43,820 --> 00:07:45,820
Why do you cry, Mama?

83
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:52,120
I'm about to be welcomed
into the Sun God's embrace!

84
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:56,410
You know being chosen
as a sacrifice is a wonderful thing!

85
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:04,130
Thank you for raising me, Mama.

86
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,300
Mousse!

87
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:13,010
If this is a nightmare,
please let me wake up!

88
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,180
Dammit!

89
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:16,930
Go away!

90
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,150
Disappear!

91
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,940
Great Warrior Kalgara...

92
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,990
Seto...

93
00:08:26,990 --> 00:08:30,360
I wanted to be like you someday...

94
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:36,080
I wanted to fight to protect
this land as a brave warrior!

95
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,040
I don't wanna die because
of something like this!

96
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,340
You're amazing, Commodore!

97
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:53,050
There really was an island
in these waters!

98
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:56,270
Yes, what a relief.
We can ride out the storm here.

99
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:59,600
So you guys really
didn't hear anything?

100
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:02,940
Nope. None of us
heard any bells. Right?

101
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:06,280
Yeah! You must've been
hearing things, Commodore!

102
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:15,580
What a magnificent forest!

103
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:18,160
I hope we find some good
research materials!

104
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:30,130
Commodore! Was that
the sound you heard?!

105
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:33,090
Hey, now! Don't tease me!

106
00:09:33,090 --> 00:09:37,100
I'd never mistake what I heard earlier
for these weird birdcalls!

107
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:40,480
C-Commodore! Was that...?

108
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:04,920
Wow... What a beautiful tone...

109
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:08,550
I knew it! There are people here!

110
00:10:10,050 --> 00:10:13,300
H-Hold on, Commodore! Wait!

111
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:18,720
Someone's on the ground!

112
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,600
Damn it... Intruders!

113
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:24,940
Hey, kid!

114
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:27,820
Commodore! He doesn't look right!

115
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:30,690
Hold it, kid!

116
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,110
Let go!

117
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:38,240
It's tree fever.

118
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,950
He hasn't been treated at all.

119
00:10:39,950 --> 00:10:42,500
Th-This island is bad news!

120
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,870
Doctor! Do we have any conine left?!

121
00:10:44,870 --> 00:10:47,840
Inject this boy and
the rest of us immediately!

122
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:54,800
This is bad.

123
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:58,260
It's even eating away at the crops...

124
00:11:00,890 --> 00:11:03,430
Commodore! Everyone inside is sick!

125
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,780
Bring the girl to the altar!

126
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,950
God of the Sun...

127
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:26,290
God of the Rain...

128
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,580
God of the Forest...

129
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:31,420
God of the Earth...

130
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:39,350
In exchange for this girl's life,
please save our village!

131
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,730
It's God Kashi!

132
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:59,240
Mousse!

133
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,450
Let her go! It's for the village!

134
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:06,040
God Kashi has such a divine form!

135
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,170
Please save my mother!

136
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:13,710
Please save my son and father!

137
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:17,340
What the...?! Something fell!

138
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,470
What's that?!

139
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:39,280
What in the world?! Who is that?!

140
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,240
God Kashi!

141
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,660
Godkiller!

142
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:50,290
This ceremony is over.

143
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,290
You must've been terrified.

144
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:53,670
You're safe now.

145
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,670
There's no need for you to die.

146
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:01,550
God Kashi! Please forgive us!

147
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:03,510
We're all going to be cursed!

148
00:13:03,510 --> 00:13:04,350
Kill her!

149
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:08,020
Offer more sacrifices to the gods
before we incur their wrath!

150
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,810
Kalgara!

151
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:12,270
Kill him!

152
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:12,270
Sounds like he did something bad...

153
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:14,060
They're really freaking out!

154
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:16,780
Commodore... what did you
get yourself into now?!

155
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:18,280
He killed a god?

156
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,490
What does that mean?!

157
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:22,990
He shouldn't be messing
around with tribal rituals!

158
00:13:22,990 --> 00:13:26,490
Quell the wrath of the gods,
Great Warrior Kalgara!

159
00:13:26,990 --> 00:13:30,580
I am an explorer from
the North Blue, Mont Blanc No–

160
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:33,580
It doesn't matter who you are!

161
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:34,880
You must be eliminated!

162
00:13:35,670 --> 00:13:40,590
Eliminated? Like every crucial ember
of progress you've snuffed out?

163
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:44,850
You have no right to preach to us!
Atone to the gods where you stand!

164
00:13:45,350 --> 00:13:46,810
Who is that man?!

165
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:48,720
He's holding his own against Kalgara!

166
00:13:56,770 --> 00:13:59,820
There! Use that knife to take your life!

167
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:02,950
What?!

168
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:07,370
You're a sacrifice meant to save our village,
yet now you're crying because you want to live.

169
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:08,740
Have you no shame?!

170
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,250
Don't be a fool!

171
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:16,960
Stop!

172
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,980
C-Commodore!

173
00:14:39,190 --> 00:14:42,780
For centuries, the people of this island
have upheld the commandment

174
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:45,660
that all intruders must be punished!

175
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,700
What's more, you are a godkiller!

176
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,790
Your death alone won't be enough!

177
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:54,420
You and all your men
will pay with your lives!

178
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:58,540
"Lives" this, "sacrifices" that!

179
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:00,880
Do you think those make
your gods happy?!

180
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:04,930
This ceremony is an affront
to humanity's progress!

181
00:15:04,930 --> 00:15:07,720
I won't stand for it any longer!

182
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:13,890
This is an insult to all
the adventurers and researchers

183
00:15:13,890 --> 00:15:17,310
who have set out to sea in the hopes
of bringing people happiness!

184
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:21,190
If your gods value people's lives,

185
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:25,360
then wouldn't they have contempt
for these ceremonies too?!

186
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:30,200
Give me some time!

187
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:36,290
I'll banish this
so-called curse of yours!

188
00:15:36,290 --> 00:15:40,880
And if I can't, you can deal
with us as you see fit!

189
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,920
What nonsense!

190
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,670
You think you're a god or something?!

191
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:51,600
In return, if I do save
this village from tragedy,

192
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:54,060
swear to me you'll abolish this ritual!

193
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,140
Are you finished?

194
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,650
Such nonsense!

195
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:00,940
Your life ends here!

196
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:02,360
Let him try!

197
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:04,900
H-Huh?

198
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,070
What are you saying?!

199
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,780
He has until tomorrow evening.
If he fails, their lives are forfeit.

200
00:16:11,530 --> 00:16:13,740
That's all I need!

201
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:22,540
Come sunset tomorrow,
it's "goodbye, world!"

202
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,710
Have faith in the commodore!

203
00:16:25,710 --> 00:16:27,340
Say, miss.

204
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:30,720
You must have it pretty rough too,
being born in this village.

205
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:31,890
Yeah!

206
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:34,680
With your looks, you could have
married an aristocrat!

207
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:37,060
Knock it off, guys!
Can't you read the room?!

208
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:38,560
Who is he?

209
00:16:39,310 --> 00:16:41,480
Oh, you mean the commodore?

210
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:43,360
That's Mont Blanc Noland.

211
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:47,400
A renowned explorer, and a botanist.

212
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:52,450
He visits uncharted islands to
document and research new plants.

213
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:55,120
He's pretty much a hero back home.

214
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,620
But he's too kindhearted...

215
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:00,870
His biggest flaw is that
he can't ignore stuff like this!

216
00:17:00,870 --> 00:17:02,960
We do trust him, though!

217
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:08,630
Why didn't you let Kalgara kill him?!

218
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:11,720
The answer will make
itself known tomorrow.

219
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:14,220
He says he'll save our village.

220
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:16,140
There is no harm in waiting.

221
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,890
How can you be so carefree?!

222
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:22,100
You'll listen to him,
but not to the priest's last words?!

223
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:25,570
Kalgara! Say something!

224
00:17:25,570 --> 00:17:28,280
If I sense the village
is in even the slightest danger,

225
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:32,950
I'll take that man's head
before sunset tomorrow.

226
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:37,370
I do not have the power
to hear the voices of the gods...

227
00:17:37,950 --> 00:17:38,790
However...

228
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:44,280
even I can hear the words
of an earnest man.

229
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:45,840
That is all.

230
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:53,050
Should you really be up?

231
00:17:53,050 --> 00:17:53,840
I'm all better...

232
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:58,020
Great Warrior Kalgara...

233
00:17:58,770 --> 00:18:02,060
What does "progress" mean?

234
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:12,280
Here we are!

235
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,200
A cona tree!

236
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:18,660
I'd be surprised if there
wasn't one in such a big forest!

237
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,830
Earthquake!

238
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:27,340
It's really happening!

239
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:29,250
It's God Kashi's curse!

240
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:35,390
Let us out of here!

241
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:49,070
This is bad...

242
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:51,740
The forest floor has sunk...

243
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:54,200
It looks like the island
is about to tear apart!

244
00:19:04,460 --> 00:19:05,830
Aren't you a fine sight?

245
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:10,500
It seems the gods have delivered you
a crushing blow themselves!

246
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:14,880
In that case, these gods...

247
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:18,010
aren't that great... after all...

248
00:19:18,010 --> 00:19:22,220
They don't even have the strength...
to kill a single person...

249
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:27,350
You're stubborn.

250
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:30,110
Sorry, but could you get lost?

251
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:32,690
I don't feel like looking at you!

252
00:19:32,690 --> 00:19:36,200
I... must hurry to the village!

253
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,160
Amusing.

254
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,830
I think I'll watch this play out.

255
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,580
Squirm out if you can!

256
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:47,580
Another warrior has perished...

257
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:49,580
And right after that earthquake...

258
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:50,670
Damn it!

259
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:57,880
You're the evil spirits!

260
00:19:57,880 --> 00:20:00,890
We'll decide your fate right now!

261
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:00,890
Th-This wasn't the agreement! Stop!

262
00:20:00,890 --> 00:20:02,180
Stop!

263
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,180
Look out!

264
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,230
Seto! Move aside!

265
00:20:11,230 --> 00:20:12,230
What are you doing?!

266
00:20:13,110 --> 00:20:15,860
The Shandian warriors I look up to...

267
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:19,070
have much more pride than this!

268
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:21,240
Kid...

269
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:26,870
When this sun lowers in the west
and sinks once again...

270
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:32,090
your men's lives will be
offered to the gods!

271
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,550
Damn it!

272
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:49,730
The earth certainly
swallowed you up quite nicely!

273
00:20:49,730 --> 00:20:51,730
Truly an act of the gods!

274
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:54,150
That you're still alive is beyond belief!

275
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,740
He shifted the earth?!

276
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,590
Prepare for the ceremony!

277
00:21:22,590 --> 00:21:25,060
Take every last sacrifice to the altar!

278
00:21:25,470 --> 00:21:26,890
Hey, wait a little longer!

279
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:30,770
The commodore will be back!
Just two more hours! No, one hour! Please!

280
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:33,100
Why do we have to be
burned at the stake?!

281
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,610
The sun is setting.

282
00:21:36,610 --> 00:21:38,610
The ceremony
should be starting soon.

283
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,610
How pathetic!

284
00:21:43,370 --> 00:21:48,200
Is this wretch the same man
who defied the gods?

285
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:51,080
What are you so afraid of?

286
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,250
What?!

287
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:55,460
You tremble before intangible fears,

288
00:21:55,460 --> 00:21:58,630
throwing away people's lives
for a false sense of comfort!

289
00:21:58,630 --> 00:22:00,220
False sense of comfort?!

290
00:22:00,670 --> 00:22:03,550
Your sacrifices are nothing
but pointless deaths!

291
00:22:08,890 --> 00:22:14,020
We have lived this way
for centuries now!

292
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:16,610
That doesn't mean it's right!

293
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,940
Silence, outsider!

294
00:22:21,950 --> 00:22:25,410
However great your gods may be,

295
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:28,580
people's lives are even more sacred!

296
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:33,420
Take the sacrifices to the altar!

297
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:36,590
Burn them at the stake
and send them into the heavens!

298
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:44,050
Commodore!

299
00:22:44,050 --> 00:22:46,430
We're gonna be burned alive!

300
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:51,810
You can send an
innocent girl to her death...

301
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:57,480
without any second thoughts,
so I doubt you'd understand!

302
00:22:57,860 --> 00:23:01,280
What you're doing is inhuman!

303
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:06,780
No second thoughts, you say?

304
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:11,370
The girl from yesterday...

305
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:14,660
was my daughter!

306
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:21,340
You would tell your own
daughter to end her life?!

307
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:26,640
You're the ones who can't
understand the immense power

308
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:29,070
of our priest's divine words!

309
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,180
It is our village's
sacred duty to obey them!

310
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:35,890
I can't plead for her life
just because she's my daughter!

311
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:46,570
It's smaller... It must be
the child of God Kashi!

312
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:51,450
The gods' own blood has come
to pass judgment on you!

313
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:54,160
Judgment, my ass!

314
00:23:55,870 --> 00:24:01,130
Sixty years ago, we lost hundreds
of thousands of lives in our homeland

315
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:05,840
to the same tree fever
that is ravaging your village now!

316
00:24:06,220 --> 00:24:10,800
However! In recent years, we've had
absolutely no deaths to this disease!

317
00:24:11,510 --> 00:24:13,970
Do you know why?!

318
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:18,140
Because we discovered a cure for it!

319
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:22,650
What I'm holding in my right hand
is the bark of a cona tree!

320
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:27,490
The conine I can extract
from it is the cure!

321
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:31,870
If I return with this,
I can save the village!

322
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:40,210
Do you know how much time has
been spent by people all around the world,

323
00:24:40,210 --> 00:24:44,840
and how many victims
there have been?!

324
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:50,090
Your people are disregarding
the incredible progress we've made!

325
00:24:50,090 --> 00:24:57,730
That's why I'm saying your "ceremonies"
are an affront to humanity's progress!

326
00:24:58,020 --> 00:25:04,150
Will I die by judgment,
or by accident?!

327
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:08,990
Will your village die
by curse, or by disease?!

328
00:25:08,990 --> 00:25:13,450
Are you that afraid of your gods?!

329
00:25:15,290 --> 00:25:19,330
Even I can hear the words
of an earnest man.

330
00:25:22,460 --> 00:25:23,630
Tell me...

331
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,470
what did I just kill?!

332
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:30,970
A snake.

333
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:32,260
No!

334
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:37,470
I broke our commandments
and felled a god!

335
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:44,730
But you call it a snake, and our
deadly curse a curable disease!

336
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:54,570
Will you really save
my beloved village?!

337
00:25:54,570 --> 00:25:56,660
Can you save it?!

338
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,000
I can!

